{{notability|date=November 2016}} {{Infobox military person |name=Karl Prümm |birth_date=12 July 1917 |death_date={{death date and age|1999|1|10|1917|7|12|df=y}} |birth_place=[[Trier]] |death_place= |image= |caption= |nickname= |allegiance={{flag|Nazi Germany}} |branch=[[German Army (Wehrmacht)|Heer]] |serviceyears=1937–45 |rank=[[Hauptmann]] |commands= |unit=Grenadier-Regiment 105 |battles=[[World War II]] *[[Battle of Greece]] *[[Operation Barbarossa]] *[[Siege of Sevastopol (1941–1942)]] *[[Battles of Rzhev]] *[[Battle of Kursk]] |awards=[[Knight's Cross of the Iron Cross]] |laterwork=}}
'''Karl Prümm''' (12 July 1917 – 10 January 1999) was a highly decorated [[Hauptmann]] in the [[Wehrmacht]] during [[World War II]] and a recipient of the [[Knight's Cross of the Iron Cross]]. The Knight's Cross of the Iron Cross was awarded to recognise extreme battlefield bravery or successful military leadership.
==Awards and decorations== * [[Iron Cross]] (1939) ** 2nd Class (31 August 1941) ** 1st Class (25 November 1941) * [[Infantry Assault Badge]] (21 September 1941) * [[Wound Badge]] (1939) ** in Black (21 September 1941) ** in Silver (9 February 1942) ** in Gold (5 August 1942) * [[Crimea Shield]] (23 August 1942) * [[Close Combat Clasp]] ** in Bronze (?) ** in Silver (21 January 1944) * [[German Cross]] in Gold (24 December 1942) * [[Knight's Cross of the Iron Cross]] on 21 May 1943 as ''[[Oberleutnant]]'' and chief of the 7./Grenadier-Regiment 105<ref>Fellgiebel 2000, p. 282.</ref>
